                <h3>Non-Infectious Diseases</h3>
                <p>Diseases like diabetes and autoimmune disorders can also occur, these occur due to body cell or organ malfunction rather than disease-causing agents and can have genetic or environmental causes. Diabetes is a condition where the body is unable to use sugar, resulting in sugar accumulating in the bloodstream, constant weakness and organ damage among other serious health effects. Autoimmune disorders occur when the body's own immune cells start to target normal body cells, causing organ damage. Hypertension is when blood pressure gets too high, damaging arteries that transport blood, making them less elastic and decreasing blood flow, resulting in heart attacks, strokes and other problems when blood vessels block or burst. The causes are many and can include age, genetics, obesity, lack of physical activity and a high-salt diet among other risk factors. Dementia is a general term for impaired ability to think and includes conditions like Alzheimer's and Parkinson's disease, which differ in symptoms and causes but all affect the brain.</p><br />
